<section class="service-main">
  <div class="service-main-grid">

    <div class="service-content">

      <!-- Overview -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">Overview</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">Why Pain Needs a <em>Multi-Modal Approach</em></h2>
        <p class="content-p">
          Pain is not a single condition — it is a complex signal from the body that varies enormously in origin, character, and severity. A simple painkiller rarely addresses the root cause. Dr. Sarish Sharma's pain management approach is built on identifying <strong>exactly what type of pain the patient has</strong> and deploying the most targeted combination of interventions to eliminate it.
        </p>
        <p class="content-p">
          Rather than relying on long-term oral medication alone, the multimodal approach combines <strong>targeted injections, nerve blocks, medication optimisation, physiotherapy, and nutritional correction</strong> — addressing pain from every angle simultaneously for faster, more lasting relief.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 4 Pain Types -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">Types of Pain Treated</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">Four Categories of Pain <em>We Address</em></h2>

        <div class="pain-cards">
          <div class="pain-card neuropathic">
            <div class="pain-card-num">01</div>
            <div class="pain-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i></div>
            <h4>Neuropathic Pain</h4>
            <p>Pain originating from damaged or compressed nerves — causing burning, shooting, or electric shock sensations. Includes sciatica, cervical and lumbar radiculopathy, nerve entrapment syndromes, and post-injury nerve inflammation. Treated with targeted nerve blocks, selective nerve root blocks (SNRB), and medication optimisation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pain-card bone-pain">
            <div class="pain-card-num">02</div>
            <div class="pain-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bone"></i></div>
            <h4>Bone Pain</h4>
            <p>Deep, aching pain arising from osteoporosis, low bone mineral density (BMD), stress fractures, and delayed or non-union fractures. Extremely common in India due to widespread Vitamin D3 and B12 deficiency. Treated with intra-fracture bone marrow injections, vitamin supplementation therapy, and targeted bone-strengthening protocols.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pain-card inflammatory">
            <div class="pain-card-num">03</div>
            <div class="pain-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-fire"></i></div>
            <h4>Inflammatory & Degenerative Pain</h4>
            <p>Pain from arthritis, joint degeneration, disc disease, tendinopathy, and bursitis — driven by chronic inflammation. Includes knee, hip, shoulder, elbow, wrist and spine pain. Treated with non-steroidal anti-inflammatory injections, PRP, viscosupplementation, epidural steroids, and physiotherapy coordination.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pain-card neoplasia">
            <div class="pain-card-num">04</div>
            <div class="pain-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></i></div>
            <h4>Neoplasia (Tumor) Pain</h4>
            <p>Musculoskeletal pain associated with tumors — whether primary bone tumors or metastatic disease causing bone pain, nerve compression, or structural compromise. Dr. Sarish Sharma provides targeted pain management support for oncology patients, coordinating with oncology teams to maximise quality of life.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Multi-Modal Approach -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">The Multi-Modal Protocol</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">Three Pillars of <em>Effective Pain Relief</em></h2>
        <p class="content-p">Each patient receives a personalised combination of these three approaches — selected based on the type, source, and severity of pain.</p>

        <div class="multimodal-grid">
          <div class="multimodal-item">
            <div class="multimodal-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-syringe"></i></div>
            <h4>Targeted Injections</h4>
            <p>Nerve blocks, PRP, epidurals, intra-articular, viscosupplementation</p>
          </div>
          <div class="multimodal-item">
            <div class="multimodal-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-pills"></i></div>
            <h4>Medication Optimisation</h4>
            <p>Right drug, right dose, right duration — reducing dependency on long-term painkillers</p>
          </div>
          <div class="multimodal-item">
            <div class="multimodal-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-person-walking"></i></div>
            <h4>Physiotherapy</h4>
            <p>Targeted rehab to address root causes and prevent recurrence of pain</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Specific Treatments -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">Specific Treatments</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">How We <em>Treat Pain</em></h2>

        <div class="approach-cards">
          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Nerve Pain</div>
              <h3>Nerve Blocks & SNRB</h3>
              <p>Selective Nerve Root Blocks (SNRB) and peripheral nerve blocks deliver <strong>anaesthetic and anti-inflammatory medication</strong> directly around the compressed or irritated nerve — providing immediate, targeted relief. Used for sciatica, cervical radiculopathy, nerve entrapment, and post-injury nerve inflammation. The procedure takes 30–45 minutes and is guided by fluoroscopy for precision.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-fire-flame-curved"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Inflammatory Pain</div>
              <h3>Non-Steroidal & Steroid Injections</h3>
              <p>For inflammatory pain — whether from arthritis, tendinopathy, or bursitis — <strong>targeted intra-articular injections</strong> deliver anti-inflammatory medication precisely to the source. Non-steroidal options are preferred for diabetic patients and those requiring repeated treatment. Epidural steroid injections address spinal nerve root inflammation with excellent outcomes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-droplet"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Regenerative</div>
              <h3>PRP & Growth Factor Therapy</h3>
              <p>Platelet-Rich Plasma (PRP) and growth factor injections harness the body's own healing mechanisms to <strong>repair damaged tissue</strong> and reduce chronic pain at the cellular level. Particularly effective for tendon injuries, ligament damage, cartilage degeneration, and chronic joint pain that hasn't responded to standard treatment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-capsules"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Nutritional</div>
              <h3>Vitamin B12, B3 & D3 Deficiency Treatment</h3>
              <p>Chronic pain is frequently worsened — or directly caused — by <strong>Vitamin B12, B3 and D3 deficiencies</strong>. B12 deficiency causes nerve inflammation and neuropathic pain. D3 deficiency leads to bone pain and muscle weakness. Dr. Sarish Sharma corrects these deficiencies through targeted injection therapy in a single session — eliminating a root cause of pain that most doctors overlook.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Who this is for -->
